      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: segmented storage breakdown bar with expandable Other",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Redesign the provider storage breakdown as a single segmented bar (one colored region per top-level item) plus a legend, replacing the old one-bar-per-item layout\r\n- Render each legend entry as a colored dot + name (primary) + size (secondary), with colors shared between the bar and the legend\r\n- Collapse items beyond the row budget into a trailing \"Other\" segment; its legend row has an expand control that reveals the folded-in item names (no colors) with sizes\r\n- Reuse the existing `Capsule` bar styling so the new bar matches the look of the old per-item bars\r\n- Show the menu's \"Storage\" row as a single normal-height line with the total size inline in a secondary color, instead of stacked below the label\r\n- Add `UsageFormatter.byteCountStringLong` and use the spelled-out units (e.g. \"1.5 gigabytes\") only on the breakdown's Total line\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- `swift build` - clean\r\n- `swift test --filter 'ProviderStorageFootprintTests|UsageFormatterTests'` - 51 tests passed\r\n- UI-only layout verified by inspecting the rendered menu (segmented bar, legend colors, \"Other\" expand/collapse, inline storage row)\r\n\r\n## Screenshots\r\n\r\nBefore:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"612\" height=\"363\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-18 at 8 07 03 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3afb6ade-79f0-4352-8fa8-bc53f517dfc4\" />\r\n\r\n<img width=\"300\" height=\"361\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-18 at 7 37 59 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b6588a14-2efe-4014-aabb-09df5473db60\" />\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"609\" height=\"516\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-18 at 8 06 43 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8b93e852-4aa4-42bf-85c9-0d4a2307c027\" />\r\n\r\n<img width=\"609\" height=\"268\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-18 at 8 06 18 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1e509cbf-3162-4beb-9f97-5199e75d4253\" />\r\n",
